post.description:
The Staff is to execute the following tasks, under the Head of Compliance discretion. Those tasks may be changed from time to time to meet the requirements of both the Bank and the local regulators including but not limited to:

-	To be mainly in charge of AML Investigation including alert investigation escalation and FATF manual monitoring, advisory on trade red flag related transaction;
-	To prepare AML investigation related reports including Suspicious Transaction Report to SBV and Transaction Monthly Report, Suspicious transaction check-sheet to MUFG Head Office;
-	To coordinate and prepare document related to financial crimes issues for on-site and off-site monitoring/inspection from local authorities, Regional Office and Head Office when necessary;
-	To cooperate and address the queries/concerns from relevant stakeholders relating to AML investigation; 
-	To conduct compliance monitoring as assigned;
-	To conduct other compliance tasks assigned by the Head of Compliance 
Report to: Head of Compliance Department

Main Responsibilities
1. Mass Recruitment:
•	Responsible for the coordination of staffing and recruitment processes of the firm;
•	Connect across RSM team within the firm to identify hiring needs;
•	CV screening and in coordination with Communication team;
•	Keep track the list of qualified candidates together with HRBPs.
2. Experienced hires:
•	Post jobs following the approval from workforce requisitions on all recruitment channels (LinkedIn, VNworks, career site, external executives search…);
•	Arrange test, interviews;
•	Follow up with the result of selection process;
•	Follow up with candidate on signing offer letters;
•	Prepare candidate pools/database to adapt with annual recruitment needs of respective functions;
•	Manage the contracts with LinkedIn, Headhunters, Vietnamworks and other jobs posts sites.
3. Onboarding process:
•	Plan onboarding strategies and perform new employees’ orientation to deliver an exceptional first-day experience at RSM Vietnam;
•	Update the profile of candidates database to RSM pool (using Base E-hiring tool);
•	Send email to support functions to prepare logistics for new staffs joining;
•	Provide necessary documents to C&B to open personnel files including: workforce requisition form, CV, JD, Interview form, test result, approval, offer letters.
4. Branding:
•	Collaborate with in Talent Acquisition Team to enhance awareness and understanding of RSM Brand name by support holding branding activities such as university tour for potential students, career fairs, webinar, etc.;
•	Attend and contribute to the career events, office visit events, job fairs;
•	Maintain good relationship with student clubs;
5. Others:
•	Conduct and analyze exit interviews and make actionable recommendations based on data;
•	Gather and analyze data with useful HR metrics.

* DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES

1.	To assist (Snr) Department Manager to manage daily operation of the stores to ensure smooth running with achievement of sales target and deliver the highest level of service including but not limited to:

•	Manage and motivate sales team to increase sales volume;
•	Provide training and coaching alongside with HR Dept. to maintain sales service at required level;
•	Conduct store inspection regularly to identify and solve urgent or arising issues;
•	Check and control stocks;
•	Handle customer complaints or inquiries;

2.	To assist (Snr) Department Manager to manage brands by:

•	Conduct market research and analysis on competitors’ stores;
•	Evaluate sales performance of each brand;
•	Negotiate with suppliers for the most favorable terms and to plan major vendor programs in important growth areas. If necessary, co-ordinate and conduct business meetings with suppliers/vendors and prepare business correspondence and reports;
•	Set-up brand selection procedure and propose in/out brands; 
•	Check and control product quality, quantity and origins;
•	Control visual merchandising of each brand; 
•	Ensure that staff and promoters observe safety and security procedures;
•	Report any sales floor operation issues (i.e. shoplifting, accident, etc.) to security personnel and attend to the necessary follow-up action. 

3.	To assist (Snr) Department Manager to plan and manage the department’s P&L: 

•	Analyze and interpret trends to facilitate planning;
•	Provide and analyze sales, profit and stock figures and forecast future sales;
•	Create business plan and sales target for the department;
•	Plan and forecast fashion and demand trends, recommend new merchandise mix and (new) suppliers to achieve the sales target;
•	Review purchases regularly and provide recommendations on appropriate actions to be taken, manage physical stock takes and regular stock checks;
•	Ensure that all purchase orders, goods returns are duly completed and processed according to established procedures;
•	Facilitate smooth movement of stocks to and from the sales floor. Effect shortage control audits.

4.	To assist (Snr) Department Manager to collaborate with Advertising & Promotion Division to conduct marketing activities:

•	Determine marketing strategy changes;
•	Organize promotions programs, special displays and events;
•	Analyze and evaluate sales result after each program;
•	Prepare and execute advertising and promotion plans, budgets and schedules; plan and execute effective merchandise zoning, layout and display by working closely with the Visual Display team and vendors so as to present the merchandise in an exciting and interesting manner to portray the desired concept and theme;
•	Provide feedback to department manager on display locations and fixtures to maximize visual impact; feedback on point of sale, publicity on the effectiveness of A&P programs. 

5.	To comply with the Company’s rules and regulations. Any act for bribes and the Company’s information leaking out is totally unacceptable.  

6.	To undertake any other activities required of the post holder by the Company;

1. MÔ TẢ CÔNG VIỆC
•	Chịu trách nhiệm quản lý, định hướng chiến lược và giám sát tất cả hoạt động bán hàng và đảm bảo các hoạt động phù hợp với chính sách, hướng dẫn, thủ tục của công ty để đạt được mục tiêu kinh doanh.
•	Chịu trách nhiệm tạo ra doanh số qua các kênh: Hợp đồng tài khoản doanh nghiệp dài hạn; Đại lý thẻ quà tặng(voucher); Hợp tác với các đối tác thương mại cho mục đích quảng cáo, thanh toán, tài trợ, v.v

2. TRÁCH NHIỆM CHÍNH
•	Quản lý điều hành và chịu trách nhiệm chung công việc của phòng ban Sales & Partnership;
•	Tổ chức triển khai hiệu quả các hoạt động đối ngoại, hợp tác tới đối tác của Golden Gate Restaurant Group trên toàn quốc nhằm thúc đẩy doanh số mô hình kinh doanh tài khoản doanh nghiệp;
•	Lập kế hoạch và triển khai quản lý đối tác, xây dựng doanh số bán hàng thông qua các chương trình hợp tác thương mại; đại lý thẻ quà tặng tiền mặt.
•	Lập chiến lược, tiến hành tiếp cận, mở rộng, phát triển quan hệ với các đối tác tiềm năng; 
•	Quản lý, chăm sóc và phát triển nguồn đối tác chiến lược của tập đoàn trên toàn quốc.
•	Thiết lập các các chỉ số đánh giá hoạt động chính để giúp theo dõi các mục tiêu và đánh giá hiệu suất bán hàng bằng các báo cáo hiệu suất. 
•	Đảm bảo chỉ tiêu kinh doanh của tập đoàn và báo cáo cho Quản lý trực tiếp hoặc Ban lãnh đạo;

The position is responsible for developing and executing category portfolio to ensure segment business growth as plan:
- Accountable for category / product portfolio innovation roadmap in aligned with regional and local innovation plan to fulfill the customer’s need;
- Work closely with regional marketing team to develop new products including concept development, packaging, product launch program;
- Act as key contact point to coordinate with cross functions to run innovation project smoothly (regional marketing, local operation, sales, finance, customer services…);
- Responsible for brand performance and competitive position in the market including volume & value growth, market share, distribution, competitive pricing and profit margin;
- Responsible to manage all aspects of brands including brand image, packaging, marketing materials, product visibility in the shop;
- Monitor product quality performance and propose action to fix if quality issue happens through working closely with sales team, technical services, operation and customers;
- Conduct market survey to understand customer’s satisfaction level on the portfolio / product performance;
- Ensure products’ certificates to be up to date and valid for providing to customers;
- Propose and lead trade campaign to ensure the brand growth as segment business strategy;
- Responsible to build and execute project marketing activities;
- Support and align with Marketing Director to run ad – hoc activities if have;
- ‘Love’ in paints, colors and architectures.

•	Define and implement the sales strategy, overseeing the full sales cycle from identifying opportunities to successfully closing deals; 
•	Monitors the effectiveness of the recruitment/retention process and advises/makes modifications as necessary with the collaboration of the Deputy and Head of Sales to ensure that targets are met on a monthly and quarterly basis; 
•	Consolidates and reviews sales and marketing reports, identifies trends, and advises the Deputy/Head of Sales of any changes to the agents operating procedure or business plan as necessary in order to improve the agent’s effectiveness & Customer journey; 
•	Advise the Marketing Section to modify its marketing approach as necessary to support changes in established sales efforts. 
•	Generate leads and proactive sales by executing against your promotional and networking events and activities; 
•	Build relationships with potential clients and brokers to sell them our added-value services and products; 
•	Maximize sales performance for your area and ensure critical KPIs are met and exceeded; 
•	Trains new and current agents staff on agent’s relationship techniques and established agent recruitment procedures. 
•	Lead and develop capability for the team to excel with their career in Real Estate.

. Responsible for the operation of logistics activities of import/export, cross-border, e-commerce cargo…
. Responsible for communicating with overseas offices/agents for logistics consulting; quotation; building and minimizing cost of logistics jobs;
. Formulate and optimize SOP standard operating procedures and service plans;
. Following of payment of logistics clients;
. Responsible for the daily management of the operation, training of staff;
. Making sure smooth and timely operation of logistics department;
. Good communication and cooperative relations with suppliers, good suppliers maintenance and assessment; good connection with related authorities;
. Perform other tasks arranged by the leadership.

Thông tin tuyển dụng: 
1. Vị trí tuyển dụng: Trưởng Phòng Tài chính – Kế toán
2. Số lượng: 01 người;
3. Địa điểm làm việc: Khu dịch vụ logistics, Cảng Hàng không Quốc tế Nội Bài, xã Phú Minh, huyện Sóc Sơn, thành phố Hà Nội

*Mô tả công việc:

Quản lý điều hành và chịu trách nhiệm chung toàn bộ hoạt động của Phòng Tài chính Kế toán theo đúng chức năng, nhiệm vụ được giao, cụ thể:
- Tổ chức bộ máy kế toán phù hợp với quy mô và mô hình hoạt động của Công ty;
- Tổ chức thực hiện công tác kế toán theo chuẩn mực kế toán và chế độ kế toán Việt Nam;
- Kiểm soát doanh thu, chi phí, đánh giá hiệu quả hoạt động sản xuất kinh doanh;
- Lập BCTC (riêng lẻ và hợp nhất), báo cáo quản trị theo yêu cầu của Ban lãnh đạo Công ty;
- Phân tích BCTC hàng quý, năm nhằm tham mưu, đề xuất các biện pháp tăng cường hiệu quả hoạt động SXKD;
- Xây dựng kế hoạch tài chính và tổ chức thực hiện, đảm bảo cân đối và sử dụng nguồn vốn hiệu quả;
- Tổ chức lưu trữ tài liệu theo đúng quy định;
- Xây dựng quy chế, quy trình, quy định, văn bản hướng dẫn thuộc lĩnh vực Kế toán tài chính phù hợp với chức năng, nhiệm vụ được giao và tổ chức thực hiện;
- Tuyển dụng và đào tạo nhân sự thuộc Phòng TC-KT;
- Nhiệm vụ khác theo yêu cầu phát sinh của công việc chuyên môn.

· Develop and manage annual and multi-year budgets that are adequate for the organization’s needs including preparation of periodic budget forecasts;
· Prepare and maintain cash flow analyses as needed;
· Analyze monthly financial statements (balance sheet, income statement, and statement of cash flows) and effectively convey analysis to staff as requested;
· Process vendor payments and check requests;
· Reconcile bank accounts and general ledger accounts as assigned;
· Respond to inquiries from regarding budgets, deposits, disbursement and grant reporting requests;
· Assist in reconciling all balance sheet and income statement accounts on a monthly/quarterly basis as indicated by the monthly closing schedule;
· Work closely with GM and to set, implement policies, procedures and to follow through with implementation; develop Company’s culture together.
